**Samuel Dalembert**

Samuel Dalembert is a Haitian-Canadian professional basketball player who has played in the National Basketball Association (NBA) for several teams, including the Houston Rockets. **Early Life and Career**

Dalembert was born on May 10, 1981, in Port-au-Prince, Haiti. He moved to Canada at a young age and began playing basketball in high school. He played college basketball at Seton Hall University, where he was named the Big East Defensive Player of the Year in 2001. **NBA Career**

Dalembert was drafted by the Philadelphia 76ers with the 26th overall pick in the 2001 NBA draft. He played for the 76ers from 2001 to 2010, serving as the team's starting center for several seasons. In 2010, he was traded to the Sacramento Kings, where he played for one season. In 2011, he signed with the Houston Rockets as a free agent. **Houston Rockets (2011-2012)**

Dalembert played for the Houston Rockets during the 2011-2012 NBA season. During his time with the Rockets, he averaged 7.5 points, 7.0 rebounds, and 1.7 blocks per game in 65 games. [1]
